<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:qxa="true" xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_45bb0782-9d5a-4e82-86fa-0122f0186924" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>13.2.6</sptc><title id="_10c094ff-5f9a-42ec-ad87-1d46fa2f613e">Floors and subfloor walls</title><archive-num>2019: 3.12.1.5</archive-num><subclause id="_454a47a8-7607-46f1-a12c-ca1405b6a882" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_02c2d66d-63f9-4e02-8f54-aa4390be96a9">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Floor insulation, where the floor is over an unenclosed space, must achieve the minimum <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_df96d9d7-3de3-424a-adda-992e7ed9c4fc" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6419_0.11.0.xml#_864e3397-2a73-43a6-804e-68c7599b603c" id="_3cc324e3-9e59-47cc-92ba-df7032e6dd1d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6a</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_7863056b-db44-4947-ae3e-a3175282d96d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_5982c0c0-bc20-4bb7-b2d7-aff39e529fb7">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Floor and subfloor insulation, where the floor is over an enclosed subfloor space, must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_06c1819b-2ea6-456a-adef-10ebccb7acf4">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_3d6beec5-c353-4487-b4c5-531d79541d74" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 1, be subfloor wall insulation with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_3e8b284b-33c8-4dfd-9e6c-4ba85dfb0fea" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> of R1.5; and</li><li id="_6ec80880-4ba2-4443-a272-fff5794e5322">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_d20a244c-c53a-48d4-98f0-a9774fabc260" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 2, be subfloor wall insulation in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6420_0.10.0.xml#_8509ecd9-0601-4fa0-ae12-330656b1d19b" id="_f5882426-eff3-4eb4-907e-9003fa19243c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6b</xref>; and</li><li id="_59b81730-6a4c-4724-a297-7da711027dee">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_e7e7df27-b708-4b5a-aa13-719485dc7242" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 3, be subfloor wall insulation in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6421_0.9.0.xml#_b63025c4-0d6e-47fb-a065-e8238d8a1f70" id="_7fbd9df7-2e04-4385-8712-d6675a257d55" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6c</xref>; and</li><li id="_9afd9a9e-1d01-44fd-9b70-e663f7c670ec">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_069f93c4-c8bd-404d-8af4-5019314744c3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 4, be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6422_0.15.0.xml#_426f8b22-8f61-4c0e-a30b-e79d677607f2" id="_c377bba1-38db-4007-8d78-0e9964dc2392" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6d</xref>; and</li><li id="_916e0dc5-931b-4e01-95e7-7423e8dacb45">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_24512d40-5812-4299-8386-ec7939146eed" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 5, be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6423_0.14.0.xml#_0e1c7fd1-b529-4557-8c27-f2c4180b3cd1" id="_6ec9b7ec-2f9c-4444-9fa0-018ccb103f6c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6e</xref>; and</li><li id="_20e51624-2642-46e0-a6fa-7b70a49f2a16">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_e2996f81-9582-44bb-909e-8b8a00665eb2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 6, be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6424_0.12.0.xml#_d27b32c0-be17-4db1-9005-cd4ba04fd214" id="_07a9ad73-f6cf-4c63-a46c-c58a2a5b739d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6f</xref>; and</li><li id="_7a819808-50c9-4de7-9d40-e85828b31b99">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_6e1b70e4-e33c-4835-9ffb-4be35ac8db38" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 7, be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6425_0.14.0.xml#_1fda7b47-7d78-4a23-9230-055e4ca3e3f4" id="_c2d71385-ca16-48b4-b87a-1ace4259d74d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6g</xref>; and</li><li id="_c1ea244c-78ec-473d-843b-2fc4e1cd0e1c">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_bb9691bc-683a-4b69-a015-c24df9c9aa27" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 8, be in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6426_0.12.0.xml#_70a19bcb-97d2-45f8-ad1b-0d3e2f2cc0d9" id="_7b6cd346-53a8-4451-a2f0-6635688ee565" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6h</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_39f38331-6d79-4e3a-8157-3d0f65b9237c" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_52ddeb5c-a882-4cf6-a8a0-1adca636d07b">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>The thermal bridging in a metal-framed floor must be addressed by—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_7cba4d08-95c8-4f6c-b647-b96278feaebe">achieving the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1490_25.4.0.xml#_bf26e61b-dbc1-4c09-b8be-ac8d936c0ac9" id="_ddab6a18-4502-4440-b045-b579c70f3d18" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Total R-Value</xref> in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6427_0.15.0.xml#_d1379a88-2fe4-4c64-8f46-46f207cea34a" id="_0787714a-8e6a-418d-9320-5d5203ba4d11" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6i</xref>, calculated by—<ol><li>using a method that accounts for the effect of thermal bridging in a suspended floor above an enclosed subfloor space; or</li><li>using AS/NZS 4859.2 for all other floors; or</li></ol></li><li id="_39c85032-e948-4b8a-ab4c-5b1fa9459b5c">complying with one of the options in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6428_0.14.0.xml#_4d5de31c-cb59-44d4-9b0c-bab07649ed77" id="_c67ffe76-fc6b-45b9-b468-6e609ace5d8e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table 13.2.6j</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_4053b4dd-55b7-416b-9b91-1a3e5bc00799" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_67d92160-ed50-4f1e-bd7a-3b6f916444fe">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>A concrete slab-on-ground with an in-slab or in-screed heating or cooling system, must have insulation with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_6634339c-f72d-4ecf-b5b0-403ae6987921" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> greater than or equal to 1.0, installed around the vertical edge of its perimeter.</p></subclause><subclause id="_c51aecd5-9890-4934-bb2f-e17a5ecf1097" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_faeec102-95a1-4933-9783-e5659c2ddd9f">SubClause</title><num>5</num><p>A concrete slab-on-ground or the like, other than a waffle pod slab, must be insulated in accordance with the following:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_1f0b50f6-2d4a-44a4-a074-19c314a77020">In <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_eb8dd138-931e-4133-8921-9f856a125490" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zones</xref> 6 and 7—<ol><li id="_85930748-48b4-4647-8237-977952e02cf9">insulation with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_431378e6-f5a8-4d0c-8ee0-44805fd7b405" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> greater than or equal to 0.64 must be installed around the vertical edge of its perimeter; and</li><li>insulation with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_5d64aada-ccf9-4f83-87cc-589f8565057d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> greater than or equal to 0.64 must be installed underneath the slab.</li></ol></li><li id="_03934dc6-96a4-4b88-b274-1631f55de886">In <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_b468a93e-ddb1-43ad-8534-6fae77a340f1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 8—<ol><li>insulation with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_6a6f4959-310a-4362-b27d-fc14ce262053" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> greater than or equal to 1.0 must be installed around the vertical edge of its perimeter; and</li><li>insulation with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_269a1bf2-ee7a-480a-b10f-36520191c7f3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> greater than or equal to 2.0 must be installed underneath the slab.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_f1d24984-4b12-4e5b-a47c-2ab04938187b" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_4295dada-3f55-4447-9242-994a30905308">SubClause</title><num>6</num><p>Insulation required by (4), (5)(a)(i) and (5)(b)(i) must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_a6229c71-9c82-4c43-824f-dd784b07ca5e">be <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1520_0.5.0.xml#_787642fb-810b-4dc9-8ea9-f54fcfbc19e1" id="_f4069ea1-4807-4c97-886c-378760142be4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">water resistant</xref>; and</li><li id="_26f970f6-b467-40b0-9c85-f2a86fa2d6be">be continuous from the adjacent finished ground level—<ol><li>to a depth of greater than or equal to 300 mm; or</li><li>for at least the full depth of the vertical edge of the concrete slab-on-ground (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/926_0.6.0.xml#_093dfc70-fae0-4145-8b44-ca0912762b49" id="_055e529e-f98a-42a1-9931-819396a6d974" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 13.2.6</xref>).</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_d0dac61c-de5e-4fc2-9d81-6ca4982b3975" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_73fea095-7cc3-452b-9d59-b6083bc583e9">SubClause</title><num>7</num><p>The requirements of (4) do not apply to an in-screed heating or cooling system used solely in a bathroom, amenity area or the like.</p></subclause><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6419_0.11.0.xml" graph="None" id="_864e3397-2a73-43a6-804e-68c7599b603c"><num/><title id="_66aa50bf-8425-4a21-939a-4021aa3f94f3"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6420_0.10.0.xml" graph="None" id="_8509ecd9-0601-4fa0-ae12-330656b1d19b"><num/><title id="_cfbcfa6e-ec8a-4dc4-ace0-a486743f19fd"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6421_0.9.0.xml" graph="None" id="_b63025c4-0d6e-47fb-a065-e8238d8a1f70"><num/><title id="_5a358916-5c77-44b5-8627-5b32d1e68840"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6422_0.15.0.xml" graph="None" id="_426f8b22-8f61-4c0e-a30b-e79d677607f2"><num/><title id="_16ccf2e0-5903-4415-9c5f-a7590a7a45a4"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6423_0.14.0.xml" graph="None" id="_0e1c7fd1-b529-4557-8c27-f2c4180b3cd1"><num/><title id="_b2b4915b-7031-406f-aa09-42a97aa19cd7"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6424_0.12.0.xml" graph="None" id="_d27b32c0-be17-4db1-9005-cd4ba04fd214"><num/><title id="_4e8986b7-d8c8-4e86-941f-2c62793abb4f"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6425_0.14.0.xml" graph="None" id="_1fda7b47-7d78-4a23-9230-055e4ca3e3f4"><num/><title id="_07bbf17e-0056-41a2-ace3-869bb46c955b"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6426_0.12.0.xml" graph="None" id="_70a19bcb-97d2-45f8-ad1b-0d3e2f2cc0d9"><num/><title id="_18f725d5-ef79-4929-bd3f-5acb87cbdc00"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6427_0.15.0.xml" graph="None" id="_d1379a88-2fe4-4c64-8f46-46f207cea34a"><num/><title id="_e21367b0-0058-4d88-907e-af688a2f1971"/></table-reference><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6428_0.14.0.xml" graph="None" id="_4d5de31c-cb59-44d4-9b0c-bab07649ed77"><num/><title id="_47527ebf-cafb-4503-a3a8-85315c415ec7"/></table-reference><table-reference author="Brandon Kiem" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/6429_0.6.0.xml" dateTime="2022-01-31T12:17:36" graph="None" id="_8bfcb209-90fd-4ba9-9895-f0b997e0a5e6" type="insert"><num/><title id="_1c48f4ad-6b18-45ae-a630-ce7eb42b032e"/></table-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/926_0.6.0.xml" id="_093dfc70-fae0-4145-8b44-ca0912762b49"><num/><title id="_22aebc48-a2bf-4072-8773-e741b208e5e6"/></image-reference><callout id="_d276fb40-8d44-4d9d-a767-b32aafce6be4"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><ul outputclass="numbered"><li>For 13.2.6(3) the effect of thermal bridging through repeating framing elements must be considered when calculating the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1490_25.4.0.xml#_bf26e61b-dbc1-4c09-b8be-ac8d936c0ac9" id="_18ec6be1-94f5-435c-b2a8-32e1c7660e45" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Total R-Value</xref> of metal-framed floors. Other types of thermal bridges may be calculated if considered significant.</li><li>13.2.6(7) provides an exemption for an in-screed heating or cooling system used solely in bathrooms, amenity areas and the like, as these are typically small areas.</li><li>Care should be taken to ensure that the type of termite management system selected is compatible with the slab edge insulation.</li></ul></callout></clause>